    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Large circular discs or trumpet-like objects that are placed in or on the ear. Examples are Precolumbian works that may be part of or a type of earspool.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093897/Metropolitan Museum of Art [online] (2001-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Grote ronde schijven of trompetachtige objecten die in of op het oor worden aangebracht. Voorbeelden zijn precolumbiaanse werken die misschien onderdeel waren van een soort oorspoel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Grandes discos circulares u objetos parecidos a una trompeta que se colocan en o sobre la oreja. Ejemplos de ello son las obras precolombinas que pueden ser parte o un tipo de orejera.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tlamantli yahyahualtic huan patlachtic zo tlamantli cencah quence trompeta tlen motlalia pan tonacaz zo iihtico tonacaz. Tlamanextilli tlen ni quence tlamantli tlamahchihchihualli ipan cahuitl precolombinos tlen hueli eli ce achi tlen topipilol.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
